<body>

<p><b>Australia: Gentoo Mini-conf in Melbourne</b></p>

<p>
<uri link="http://linux.conf.au">linux.conf.au</uri>, Australia's annual 
technical conference about Free Software. Fun, informal, and seriously 
technical, linux.conf.au draws together Free and Open Source Software 
developers from across the world. It will be held from January 28th to 
February 2nd, 2008 at the University of Melbourne. This year it will also 
feature a half-day mini-conf about Gentoo on Tuesday 29th.
</p>

<p>
Some talks have been organized, but more are needed. There are speaking slots 
for 50 minute, 25 minute, or 10 minute lightning talks. If you are interested 
in attending or presenting, please contact 
<mail link="mark_alec@gentoo.org">Mark Kowarsky</mail>.
</p>

